The evidence with the title 'What Einstein, Twain, & forty eight others said about school ... ' says Education is an admirable thing, but it is well to remember from time to time  ... A man who has never gone to school may steal from a freight car; but if he  ... I wonder whether if i had an education i should have been more or less a fool than i am.  ... Spoon feeding in the long run teaches us nothing but the shape of the spoon. 
